summary: researchers found that nitrofurantoin was less effective than other antibiotics for treatment of UTI in a large cohort of older women regardless of the women’s estimated kidney function. the authors of this cohort study found that migrants are at increased risk of psychotic disorders. ittrick–Wheelock syndrome is a new human coronavirus that causes severe respiratory illness. 82-year-old man was found to have multiple aneurysms of his coronary arteries after undergoing investigations for exercise intolerance.
